President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Richard M. Lobo is nominated for Director of the International Broadcasting Bureau. He has a background in broadcasting and has served as chairman of the Florida Public Broadcasting Service Inc. Lowell Junkins is nominated as Chairman and Member of the Board of Directors for the Federal Agricultural Mortgage Corporation. He has experience as an Iowa State Senator and currently works as a public affairs consultant. Sara L. Faivre-Davis is nominated as a Member of the Board of Directors for the Federal Agricultural Mortgage Corporation. She has experience in genetics and animal science, and currently owns a cattle ranch and a livestock genetic improvement company.